service.name: Pharmaceutical Benefits Scheme Safety Net
service.TODO: Is this a service for DHS or TAX???
service.description:
The Pharmaceutical Benefits Scheme Safety Net reduces the cost of prescription medicines for individuals and families once the PBS Safety Net threshold has been reached.  Each year the Commonwealth (the Department of Health) sets a Safety Net threshold amount, one each for: 
concession card holders (referred to as concession), people who don't hold a concession card (referred to as general).
